  "original_title": "School to function on 3-days a week",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "School to function on 3-days a week",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Ministry of Education noted that from today (1) to the 5th of August all Government schools and Government Approval Private schools will operate only on three days.",
        "Accordingly, the school will be held on Monday, Tuesday, and Thursday while Wednesday and Friday school sessions will be held online.",
        "However, the Ministry of Education says that schools that do NOT have any transportation difficulties can be held on Wednesdays and Fridays with the approval of the principals and teachers and the approval of the Regional Education Directors.",
        "Considering the current situation in the schools, the Ministry of Education also said that amended timetables should be prepared so that every teacher can come to the school for at least three days to carry out teaching activities.",
        "Meanwhile, the date of calling for applications for the admission of children to the first grade in the year 2023 has been extended.",
        "Accordingly, the Ministry of Education announced that applications can be submitted until August 15.",
        "Meanwhile, the Deputy Director of Health Services of the Ministry of Health Dr. Hemantha Herath informs the school students to pay attention to hygiene measures due to the rise of COVID-19."
      ],
